  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomatoes</strong> into quarters</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678292541795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678292541795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678292541795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678292541795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678292541795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large pot (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678292545441-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678292545441-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678292545441-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678292545441-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678292545441-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>tomato quarters</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the vegetables have softened and are beginning to char – this is your <strong>roasted pepper & tomato</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
